A_request_to_a_cross_origin_resource_is_.message:
A request to a cross origin resource is nothing unusual.
You just have to check whether this script has a good reason to access this domain.
For example there are only a very few reasons for a userscript to contact your bank.

Please note that userscript authors can avoid this dialog by adding [url=$connect$]@connect tags[/url] to their scripts.

No matter how you'll decide, you can change your opinion at any time at the script's [url=$settings$]settings tab[/url].

Tampermonkey_External_Script_List_Access.message: Script synchronization (Tampermonkey External Script List Access)

This_sync_version_may_multiply_each_scri.message:
Unlike the 'Legacy' sync version this one synchronizes your scripts by reference to a unique ID that is created when a script is installed!

This means if you installed a script at multiple Tampermonkey instances by either another sync method or a normal script installation then this script will appear multiple times after the next sync iteration has finished.

The only way to recover is to manually remove each doubled script entry!

Do you really want to continue?
